They vowed revenge for their loss,

155
00:20:50,699 --> 00:20:52,739
while searching for the girl.

156
00:20:56,705 --> 00:20:59,205
Why would the old leader's daughter

157
00:20:59,575 --> 00:21:01,440
end up in a brothel?

158
00:21:02,845 --> 00:21:06,474
Who owns the Peony Pavilion?

159
00:21:07,282 --> 00:21:10,152
Perhaps the 'Flying
Daggers' has realized

160
00:21:10,152 --> 00:21:13,652
we were responsible for
their old leader's death.

161
00:21:14,023 --> 00:21:14,921
Forget it.

162
00:21:15,290 --> 00:21:17,392
Let's turn her over for a reward,

163
00:21:17,393 --> 00:21:19,473
and then go out for a drink.

164
00:21:20,929 --> 00:21:22,489
I have a better idea.

165
00:21:22,998 --> 00:21:24,798
Since we have some clues,

166
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:28,320
let's follow them through
for a bigger reward.

167
00:21:29,938 --> 00:21:31,778
Do you want me to do it?

168
00:21:32,775 --> 00:21:34,225
Of course, who else?

169
00:21:35,944 --> 00:21:39,812
All right. This girl is a rare beauty.

170
00:21:40,149 --> 00:21:43,050
You know I love flirting with girls.

171
00:21:46,622 --> 00:21:49,242
Don't let beauty blind your judgment.

172
00:21:49,691 --> 00:21:53,631
If I die under a skirt, I
can still flirt as a ghost.

173
00:23:38,534 --> 00:23:39,466
Who are you?

174
00:23:40,269 --> 00:23:42,103
I undressed you only yesterday.

175
00:23:42,104 --> 00:23:44,204
Have you forgotten me already?

176
00:23:44,506 --> 00:23:46,126
Why did you rescue me?

177
00:23:48,043 --> 00:23:49,313
Why do you think?

178
00:23:50,779 --> 00:23:52,699
You're an exquisite flower.

179
00:23:52,915 --> 00:23:55,406
I'll do anything to help you.

180
