I've rescued you,

189
00:24:17,573 --> 00:24:19,632
and your daggers as well.

190
00:24:23,178 --> 00:24:25,318
Why did you take such a risk?

191
00:24:25,948 --> 00:24:27,915
I hate the corrupt government

192
00:24:27,916 --> 00:24:30,136
and admire the 'Flying Daggers'.

193
00:24:31,587 --> 00:24:32,576
Much obliged.

194
00:24:34,590 --> 00:24:36,424
Why did we abandon the horses?

195
00:24:36,425 --> 00:24:38,292
Hoof prints can be easily tracked.

196
00:24:38,293 --> 00:24:40,793
I have two new horses hidden ahead.

197
00:24:40,896 --> 00:24:42,454
You've planned well.

198
00:24:43,865 --> 00:24:45,665
What's your name, Master?

199
00:24:45,834 --> 00:24:47,164
Just call me Wind.

200
00:24:47,936 --> 00:24:48,903
Wind?

201
00:24:49,338 --> 00:24:51,198
I wander around all alone,

202
00:24:51,373 --> 00:24:53,403
come and go without a trace.

203
00:24:53,475 --> 00:24:54,985
Like a carefree wind?

204
00:24:55,410 --> 00:24:58,504
No, a playful wind.

205
00:24:59,815 --> 00:25:01,339
You like to tease.

206
00:25:01,683 --> 00:25:03,713
I wonder what you look like?

207
00:25:03,752 --> 00:25:05,542
That's easy to find out.

208
00:25:05,587 --> 00:25:06,485
Here.

209
00:25:08,924 --> 00:25:09,964
Please let go.

210
00:25:10,759 --> 00:25:13,561
This isn't the Peony
Pavilion. No rules here.

211
00:25:13,562 --> 00:25:17,272
You'll know what I look
like if you touch my face.

212
00:25:18,467 --> 00:25:19,456
Come on.

213
00:25:20,502 --> 00:25:23,762
It's not respectful to
touch your face first.

214
00:25:28,844 --> 00:25:31,677
You prefer to start at the bottom.

215
00:25:32,114 --> 00:25:33,614
That's fine with me.

216
00:25:34,683 --> 00:25:37,253
You've mastered the flying technique.

217
00:25:40,455 --> 00:25:43,485
Your right hand is
skilled with a machete.

218
00:25:48,363 --> 00:25:51,853
Your left hand is powerful
with a bow and arrow.

219
00:25:58,073 --> 00:26:01,440
Your heart beats
steadily, you seem sincere.

220
00:26:01,877 --> 00:26:03,957
You can read me like a book.

221
00:26:04,713 --> 00:26:06,153
You're a brave man.

222
00:26:06,848 --> 00:26:09,078
I'm never shy around women.

223
00:26:13,855 --> 00:26:15,365
You're young, indeed.

224
