Don't let her fool you.

280
00:40:49,497 --> 00:40:50,896
Don't be absurd.

281
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:53,758
I'm in control.

282
00:40:54,702 --> 00:40:56,670
I have to get back now.

283
00:40:58,906 --> 00:41:02,506
Don't turn a game into
reality and ruin our plan.

284
00:41:02,710 --> 00:41:05,736
Who cares, as long as the plan works.

285
00:41:25,466 --> 00:41:27,376
Shall we rest for a while?

286
00:41:34,408 --> 00:41:35,568
I smell flowers.

287
00:41:52,893 --> 00:41:53,882
You told me

288
00:41:54,629 --> 00:41:57,709
you'd bring me to
where real flowers grow.

289
00:42:52,687 --> 00:42:54,667
Which is the most beautiful?

290
00:43:08,002 --> 00:43:09,092
How do I look?

291
00:43:09,670 --> 00:43:11,060
Pretty as a flower.

292
00:43:18,312 --> 00:43:20,012
Soldiers are approaching.

293
00:43:55,716 --> 00:43:57,036
I'm on your side.

294
00:43:57,385 --> 00:43:58,113
You?

295
00:43:58,319 --> 00:43:59,586
I am a Captain of the County.

296
00:43:59,587 --> 00:44:00,383
A captain?

297
00:44:02,690 --> 00:44:06,190
Nonsense. You are the
bastard who broke the jail.

298
00:46:29,637 --> 00:46:31,787
You're wounded. Is it serious?

299
00:46:33,240 --> 00:46:33,729
No.

300
00:48:22,016 --> 00:48:24,936
Was it someone from
the 'Flying Daggers'?

301
00:48:33,027 --> 00:48:34,237
It's not likely.

302
00:48:37,998 --> 00:48:38,987
Then who?

303
00:48:41,769 --> 00:48:42,799
I don't know.

304
00:48:47,307 --> 00:48:48,331
He's gone.

305
00:48:51,045 --> 00:48:54,125
I guess he doesn't
want to reveal himself.

306
00:49:37,524 --> 00:49:40,960
This time, I believe
that you're for real.

